(Summary: Background: Osimertinib resistance is the main challenge of the treatment in EGFR) Tj
T*
(mutant lung adenocarcinoma \(LUAD\). The role of N6-methyladenosine \(m6A\) modification of) Tj
T*
(circular RNAs \(circRNAs\) in osimertinib-resistant LUAD remains largely unknown. Methods:) Tj
T*
(Parental and resistant cell lines, as well as human and mouse lung tissue samples were) Tj
T*
(implemented. We used MeRIP-seq and circRNA-seq to screen the potential circRNA candidate that) Tj
T*
(influenced osimertinib resistance. The sensitivity of LUAD cells was detected by Cell Counting) Tj
T*
(Kit-8 \(CCK-8\) assay. The interaction between circRNA and proteins was validated by RNA) Tj
T*
(immunoprecipitation and RNA pulldown. We generated circRNA encapsulated in lipid nanoparticle) Tj
T*
(\(LNP\). Bioluminescence imaging assay was used for the monitoring of orthotopic transplantation) Tj
T*
(model. Results: It was observed that circRNA LMNB1 \(cLMNB1\) exhibited elevated levels of m6A) Tj
T*
(modification and diminished expression in osimertinib-resistant LUAD. cLMNB1 increased the) Tj
T*
(sensitivity of LUAD to osimertinib in vitro and in vivo. METTL3 increased the m6A modification) Tj
T*
(of cLMNB1 and inhibited its expression through the reading protein YTHDF2. cLMNB1 acted as a) Tj
